{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b375161c-e7cd-48b4-a688-3bf37cec4c83","content":"The standard format is a **YAML evaluation file** (`evaluation.yml`) with a list of scenarios. Each scenario has a natural-language user prompt and assertions about which tools the LLM should call, with what arguments, and what the final answer should contain.\n\n### Basic structure\n\n```yaml\nscenarios:\n  - name: simple_product_lookup\n    prompt: \"What is the price of the 'Wireless Mouse Pro'?\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: get_product\n        arguments:\n          name: \"Wireless Mouse Pro\"\n    expected_response_contains:\n      - \"$29.99\"\n\n  - name: multi_tool_reasoning\n    prompt: \"Which accessories are compatible with the UltraBook 15?\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: get_product\n        arguments:\n          name: \"UltraBook 15\"\n      - tool: get_compatible_accessories\n        arguments:\n          product_id: \"{{dynamic}}\"\n    expected_response_contains:\n      - \"USB-C Dock\"\n```\n\n### What makes a good evaluation question\n\n| Quality | Example |\n|---|---|\n| **Unambiguous** — one correct tool path | \"What is the weight of product SKU-1234?\" |\n| **Multi-step** — tests chaining | \"Compare the prices of X and Y\" (two `get_product` calls) |\n| **Requires reasoning** — not just passthrough | \"Which product under $50 has the best rating?\" |\n| **Tests edge cases** — missing data, no results | \"Find products in the 'Hoverboards' category\" |\n| **Tests parameter mapping** — natural language → args | \"Show me everything by Acme Corp\" → `search(manufacturer: \"Acme Corp\")` |\n\n### Tips\n\n- **Cover each tool** at least once in isolation, then in combination.\n- **Include negative cases** (queries the tools can't answer) to test graceful failure.\n- **Vary phrasing** — the same intent worded differently tests robustness.\n- **Keep expected outputs concrete** — assert on specific values, not vague patterns.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold an `evaluation.yml` tailored to your specific tool definitions?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa9a7957-3ba0-43b8-adc2-488935ed2c10","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. The user is asking a general guidance question about evaluation format for MCP server tools. Based on the custom instructions, this repository is related to skill plugins and the skill-validator. Let me provide guidance based on what I know about evaluation YAML formats for MCP skill evaluation, which is the standard used in this ecosystem.\n\nLet me provide a helpful, concise answer about evaluation format and good evaluation question practices.","outputTokens":623,"requestId":"3860:320DC4:6A626BA:72C6A25:6A03CE7E"},"id":"e6e8bdf6-6ba5-4b45-b6a8-e99f4472e878","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:21.453Z","parentId":"934f7dff-0936-42a5-a5a5-bd172a0c4ddb"}
